<plot>"Being BAWSI" shows 3rd-5th grade low income girls and their moms, from an under-served Latino community in San Jose, CA, transcend cultural and economic hurdles and transcend health and hope by being BAWSI(pronounced "bossy"). Co-founded by soccer star Brandi Chastain, BAWSI(Bay Area Women's Sports Initiative) is an after school fitness and motivation program. "Being BAWSI", shows the girls and their mothers having fun working out alongside Chastain and college women athletes that volunteer to coach, mentor and be role models for a healthy lifestyle. This film captures the power &amp; joy of being BAWSI, the results of transformation, and the dedication of women to communities</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?064120</url></doc>
